{
  "brand": "BenQ",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "BenQ MH/MW/MX/MS/MP/W/SH/TH series (ASCII protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: BenQ RS232 Command Control Reference (covers MH/MW/MX/MS/MP/W/SH/TH/Q-series).",
    "Wire: DB9 cross-over (null-modem). 9600 8N1, no flow control.",
    "Each command is wrapped CR + '*<cmd>=<value>#' + CR -> bytes: 0x0D '*' ... '#' 0x0D.",
    "Projector echoes the command back, then replies with '*<cmd>=<value>#' or '*Block item#'.",
    "Response arrives ~30-200ms after send; allow up to ~300ms when projector is warming up.",
    "Query commands use '=?' (e.g. '*pow=?#'). Responses arrive as ASCII strings: *POW=ON# / *POW=OFF#, *SOUR=HDMI#, *LTIM=1234# (hours), *LTSP=LNORM# or =ECO#, *MUTE=ON#/OFF#, *VOL=10#, *ASP=AUTO#/4:3#/16:9#/REAL#, *BRI=50#, *CON=50#, *BC=ON#/OFF# (blank), *MODELNAME=MX615#, *SERNUM=PD25P01234#, *FWVER=V01.02#, *FREEZE=ON#/OFF#."
  ],
